# ORIG TITLE    Desmond Tutu admitted to Cape Town hospital . 
# ORIG CONTENT  South African Archbishop and peace campaigner Desmond Tutu is in a Cape Town hospital being treated for a persistent infection. A statement released by his charity, the Desmond and Leah Tutu Legacy Foundation, says Tutu will receive non-surgical treatment for about five days. The Nobel Peace Prize winner previously suffered prostate cancer. 
